INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','article',0,39,46,'und',0,'<p>test</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"image-left\" src=\"http://theprecarious.com/sites/default/files/field/image/mittromney.jpg\" style=\"padding: 5px; margin-right: 5px; border-width: 2px; border-style: solid; width: 312px; height: 208px; float: left;\" title=\"hoping for a &lt;em&gt;caption&lt;/em&gt;.\">Over the last 200 years, almost entirely as a result of the U. S. union movement, workers have achieved an impressive array of protections and rights.&nbsp; Included in these are some basic rights to organize and to receive overtime pay.&nbsp; An employer cannot cheat workers out of wages, beat them, expose them to extremely dangerous or toxic environments without protection, sexually harass them, and in many cases, cannot discriminate against them.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"image-right\" src=\"http://theprecarious.com/sites/default/files/field/image/mittromney.jpg\" style=\"padding: 5px; margin-left: 5px; border-width: 2px; border-style: solid; float: right; height: 167px; width: 250px;\" title=\"and also a second caption\">It should also be noted that many laws and regulations do not apply to the agricultural industry. Not that the laws are effective, as instances of <a href=\"http://www.globalresearch.ca/index.php?context=va&amp;aid=12576\">modern day slavery</a> are found from California to Florida.&nbsp; Additionally, many U.S. territories, such as the Marianas Islands, are essentially export processing zones, where almost all worker protections found in the states are absent.&nbsp; Here workers labor under sweatshop conditions, competitively exporting goods that have a “Made in the U.S.A.” label.&nbsp; Of course, these conditions can also be found in LA, New York, and Chicago.&nbsp; The U.S. Labor Department estimates that 50% of all sewing shops in the United States are <a href=\"http://www.mtholyoke.edu/%7Enshah/fashioncrimes/Sweatshops.html\">illegal sweatshops</a>.</p>','','full_html');
